TextInput_1: It was pretty good. I just felt that the car was kind of stop/go too much for my liking for how many pedestrians there were. Like if it slowed down when there were more in it's area.

The only thing that I noticed today is how there's no indicator's in this simulation for when the car is turning. A couple times I thought the car was making a mistake, but then I figured out it was turning, but there was no indication on the car or sound that there was a turn signal used.

The stuff from the other days still applies, but one thing I wanted to point out that I don't think I did before, was that I don't like how the colors for pedestrian are light blue or just regular blue. It seems very similar, and it causes the person to take a half second and determine which blue is crossing, and what blue is not crossing.
